This paper is about reinforcement learning for task-oriented dialogue systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of user simulators, which is a common technique in reinforcement learning, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely. The paper also involves training agents to interact with humans, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data and rules, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
